# Ingestion Layer (Jetstream)

Read `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_SPEC.md` §7 for complete code patterns.

## Connection
- Primary: `wss://jetstream2.us-east.bsky.network/subscribe`
- Fallback: `wss://jetstream1.us-east.bsky.network/subscribe`
- Filter collections: `app.bsky.feed.post`, `app.bsky.feed.like`, `app.bsky.feed.repost`, `app.bsky.graph.follow`
- ALWAYS include `cursor` parameter on reconnect

## Cursor Persistence (CRITICAL)
- Save cursor to `jetstream_cursor` table every ~1000 events
- On disconnect: reconnect WITH cursor to avoid silent data gaps
- On startup: read last cursor from DB, connect with it
- If no cursor exists: connect without (will get latest events only)

## Reconnection
- Exponential backoff: 1s → 2s → 4s → ... → 60s max
- After 5 failures on primary, try fallback instance
- Log every disconnect/reconnect with timestamps and cursor value

## Event Processing
- Route events through event-processor.ts to typed handlers
- Handle: create (post/like/repost/follow), delete
- Delete handler is CRITICAL — must work before anything else
- Soft delete: set `deleted = TRUE`, never remove rows
- All handlers must be idempotent (use UPSERT patterns)

## Types
Jetstream events have: `did`, `time_us`, `kind` (commit/identity/account), `commit.operation` (create/update/delete), `commit.collection`, `commit.rkey`, `commit.record`
